                    sessions in either shorter-spaced learning (twice a week) or longer-spaced learning conditions (once a week). Their oral
                    production performance both during and after the training was related to their metalinguistic rule rehearsal ability (MRRA) and
                    working memory capacity (WMC). Multiple regression analyses revealed that MRRA predicted learnersâ training and posttest
